    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pieces of defensive armor in the form of a coat, covering the upper part of the body, having interlaced rings or overlapping plates of steel, usually over a quilted linen or leathern jacket.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Piezas de armadura defensiva en forma de abrigo que cubren la parte superior del cuerpo, con anillos entrelazados o placas de acero superpuestas, generalmente sobre una chaqueta acolchada de lino o cuero.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tlamantli tepoztli quence quechquemitl tlen quitzacua zo quipalehuia huan para axtlen ma quiahci totlacayo quence toyolixco, ica aniyoz mohmotzquitoc zo tepozpamitl tlen acero, nochipa eltoc iixco cotomitl quence tzotzolti tlachihualli ica lino zo cuetlaxtli.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
